##Under the line of impact of the epidemic training cold, 100 billion online education hot admission

The industry will undergo a shuffle

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
"I obviously am a teacher, now the net class turned me into the anchor... " recently, this kind of humorous self-deprecation on the Internet heat.

Affected by the outbreak of new crown pneumonia, offline institutions have been suspended. The Ministry of Education announced the extension of the 2020 spring school year, and advocated "no suspension of classes without suspension, " encouraging schools and training institutions to shift education and teaching to online settings, online education is gaining national attention in an unprecedented fashion.

Learning and thinking, New Oriental, excellence in education and other offline education and training institutions have suspended classes, to free online courses. On Feb. 3,5 million students attended an online class on the first day of the online education company Simian Tutor. So far, more than 20 million people have signed up for the free live streaming class.

From the performance of the US stock market and Hong Kong stock market in recent days, affected by the delayed start-up News, the education sector has appeared polarization. Most of these fell, while online education stocks were strong, with New Oriental online up more than 11 per cent at one point in mid-day trading on January 29, a record high.

Offline training frustrated

For the offline training industry, 2019 has been an eventful year, with wage arrears, closures and even absconding.

China Newsweek learned that Tianjingheng International Education Consulting (Beijing) Co. , Ltd. suspended classes from January 29 to February 1 for violating the requirement of offline training institutions during the epidemic prevention and control period, he was suspended from the Business license for conducting the art pre-college entrance examination tutoring and training activities without authorization. According to the investigation, 72 students from other places came to Beijing on January 17 and were offered painting training courses by the Educational Training Institution.

On the evening of February 6, a well-known IT training organization, Brothers Education, announced that due to the impact of the epidemic, the Beijing campus of brothers education stopped recruiting students and all employees were dismissed.

Founder Li Chao said the company has little capital reserves and has been losing money, the company had a year ago to cut costs, delayed wages, all mobilization, plan in the recruitment season after the festival to fight a turnaround, but the epidemic will be completely disrupted.

According to the information from the company, the company is affiliated to Beijing Education Consulting Co. , Ltd. , which has been established for 13 years. In 2015, the company received 125 million yuan in strategic investment from HUATU. The annual report for 2016 showed revenue of 135 million yuan and net profit of 11.696 million yuan.

Such industry-wide disasters occurred during the SARS epidemic in 2003. At that time, with the outbreak of "SARS" there was a wave of student withdrawals refund, and New Oriental has put the advance into the summer teaching, renting classrooms, printing materials, market publicity, and so on, the situation is very serious. In the end, Yu Minhong had to borrow $20 million to survive the crisis.

Guang Zheng Hang Seng analyst Huang Guan that short-term offline training industry spring recruitment stagnation, small and medium-sized enterprises cash flow risk. The outbreak coincided with the off-line training in the spring enrollment phase, and due to market sentiment, the subsequent resumption of operations or less than the normal state, and the relatively rigid operating costs, coupled with the potential for fee refunds and runs, will exacerbate the cash flow disruption of off-line training institutions.

Everbright Securities analyst Liu Kai, affected by the epidemic, New Oriental, good future, public education and other training institutions offline network temporarily closed. In the short term, the industry-wide training institutions are not only facing the pressure from the income side, but also the pressure from the rent cost, the personnel salary, the operating cost, etc. .

On the one hand, it is very difficult to go to college. Because of the college entrance examination system, the historical and cultural heritage, the reform of the new college entrance examination, and the outbreak of demand in third-and fourth-tier cities, the demand for K12 off-line training is still huge. On the other hand, it is very difficult to find jobs, in the Depression and Employment Situation, vocational training and education upgrading has become the choice of many graduates, counseling rigidity, teaching materials demand, the growth in the number of applicants all promote the rapid development of the entire market.

Online education is booming

According to public data, the domestic online education market will reach 124.9 billion yuan in 2018, and is expected to reach 310.2 billion yuan in 2022, of which K12 online education market is expected to reach 79 billion yuan in 2022.

The threshold of online education lies in brand awareness and teacher resources. At present, the cost of online education consists of R & D cost in the early stage and marketing and sales cost in the late stage. K12 online education industry in 2019 outbreak, several head of online education companies in 2019 summer vacation is expected to spend about 3 billion-4 billion yuan.

Among them, good future, Simian guidance in 2019 summer sales class enrollment of more than 1 million people, the conversion rate of special classes to regular classes about 20%-30% , regular classes renewal rate is expected to 70%-80% . New Oriental online enrolled about 200,000 students in 2019.

Recently, ape-assisted online education provided free live-streaming classes to primary and secondary school students nationwide, and New Oriental offered 1 million free live-streaming classes to primary and secondary school users nationwide, on February 10, Xueersi will launch free live and self-study classes for all subjects in the whole grade from Monday to Friday, which will be synchronized with the school time, learn from WHO and high-distance classes to 20,000 Wuhan Primary and secondary school students donated 20 million yuan winter vacation real-price live courses, netease Youdao to Wuhan Primary and secondary school students free winter vacation online courses.

"online courses are becoming more and more resource-rich, ranging from courses offered by online educational institutions to those offered online by public school teachers. Children as a whole learn a lot, " Liu, from Beijing, told China Newsweek, to a certain extent, the online course has lightened the burden of parents, teachers and students.

However, she also admitted that there are good and bad online courses, suggesting carefully selected courses, unified teaching materials, by well-known authoritative teachers to teach quality courses, schools do not have to let all teachers, there should be no rush to take online classes.

As school teachers rush into action, the advantages of online education institutions ploughing through years of live-streaming classes are starting to show. "The online course is taught by top-notch teachers, relying on big data back-feeding teaching, to create a more scientific and systematic online live courses. At the same time, online class, students can real-time video with the teacher connected to the microphone, on the screen with drag, wire and other interactive operations to complete the Exercise Fun Answer. Through grab wheat, wheat, in front of the class to answer questions, can stimulate students'interest in learning, improve self-confidence.".

Simian search, an online education unit of Simian tutorial, has more than 160 million questions and has provided 33 billion homework tutorials and 20 million hours of question answering and explanation. Simian search has provided 700 million questions and exercises, the Nation's elementary and middle school students have already spent 90 million hours practicing in the Monkey Puzzle Bank; Kozaru has calculated that there are more than 250 million correct questions every day, and more than 25 million online practice questions every day, serving more than 30 million elementary students, accumulated a large number of users high-frequency error-prone, heavy and difficult data, and a large amount of data for better design of online course products provide a strong support.

During the extended winter break period, to help students improve their overall quality, ape counseling also introduced master humanities classes and model youth said. The master humanities course, together with historian Ji Lianhai, the judges of the Chinese Poetry Conference Kang Zhen and Meng Man, military expert Zhang Zhaozhong, and other masters jointly preach and teach, enhance the humanities of students; Model Youth said the course invited Harvard law doctor Qingyun Zhan, Fudan University Associate Professor Xiong Hao, and so on, to broaden students'horizons and set great ambitions.

In response to the needs of special groups in the third year of Senior High School and the third day of junior high school, the "million-person Online large-scale exam" launched on February 15 has restored the difficulty level of the middle and senior high school entrance examination, and provided intelligent diagnostic reports and national ranking predictions.

It is reported that the total number of users of the online education of the apes has exceeded 400 million. The company has a number of online learning products, such as the online instruction of the apes and the search for problems of the Little Apes, which are tailor-made for students from online classes, intelligent exercises to problem solving, provide personalized diagnosis to help students complete the learning loop systematically and efficiently.

Everbright Securities analyst Liu Kai said the outbreak may further foster and enhance the use of online education and learning habits of students, further guidance to online transformation, K12 online education will be the next few years of the education industry's Golden Racetrack.

Li Yanli of Western securities believes that the industry will undergo a round of reshuffle, leading companies in brand awareness and teaching force still have core competitiveness, is expected to be far better than the industry average performance during the epidemic.

She analysis, New Oriental, good future and elite education the vast majority of business income from offline, estimated that February revenue accounted for about 8% of the year, the year's revenue impact is limited. Leading the first time off-line courses to move to the line, to a certain extent to ensure the survival of the source of students. If the outbreak lasts for a long time, the demand for tutorial classes for lower-grade students may be weakened, while the online price is lower than the offline one, then the annual income will be affected.

Li Yanli said that the biggest problem online is the capacity of teachers and follow-up Student Services. If online users are concentrated in an outbreak, the grooming of products and the supply of teachers need to be optimized. Therefore, after the epidemic has subsided, online growth is likely to slow. If a large number of online business transfer to the offline, the course will be able to better link up training institutions will be a certain challenge.

According to Wu Jingcao, an analyst at Guojin Securities, in most of the training scenarios, online and offline education are not substitutes for each other, but rather a collaborative relationship. What we need to look forward to in the future is not online education replacing offline education, it's about better blending of the online and offline worlds of education.
